01:10:55.118 --> 01:10:58.424
But then he starts pointing.
He starts pointing. (LAUGHING)

01:10:59.255 --> 01:11:00.490
"Why are you pointing?"

01:11:00.590 --> 01:11:02.959
"'Cause you're fat,
your fat's going everywhere.

01:11:03.059 --> 01:11:04.794
"Your fat's going everywhere."

01:11:04.894 --> 01:11:07.830
I go, "Really? My fat's going
everywhere? Well, guess what?

01:11:07.930 --> 01:11:11.009
"This fat makes your mom horny."

01:11:11.400 --> 01:11:13.079
(ALL CHEERING)

01:11:13.536 --> 01:11:15.079
(MOUTHING)

01:11:23.813 --> 01:11:25.458
And he's like... (SCREAMING)

01:11:28.451 --> 01:11:32.098
If I ask him to do something,
and he doesn't do it,

01:11:32.555 --> 01:11:34.557
like, for example, as parents,

01:11:34.657 --> 01:11:37.326
you want your kids to go
to sleep by a certain time,

01:11:37.426 --> 01:11:40.463
because you need 'em to wake up
in time to get ready for school.

01:11:40.563 --> 01:11:42.865
Frankie's cutoff is 11:00.

01:11:42.965 --> 01:11:45.668
It's pretty late,
if you ask me, for a kid.

01:11:45.768 --> 01:11:48.237
Sometimes he'll push it to midnight,
you know, play dumb.

01:11:48.337 --> 01:11:49.472
"Oh, I didn't know what time it was."

01:11:49.572 --> 01:11:52.275
"Yeah, whatever.
You're only holding a clock."

01:11:53.409 --> 01:11:55.678
But I get it. I used
to play dumb, too.

01:11:55.778 --> 01:11:58.147
So then he'll walk in his room,
and he'll say...

01:11:58.247 --> 01:12:00.516
(YAWNING) "Good night, Dad,"
and he'll close the door.

01:12:00.616 --> 01:12:01.651
(MIMICS DOOR CLOSING)

01:12:01.751 --> 01:12:03.186
And he thinks he's slick.

01:12:03.286 --> 01:12:06.255
He takes a towel, and he
starts rolling up the towel,

01:12:06.355 --> 01:12:08.157
and he puts it under the door,

01:12:08.257 --> 01:12:11.301
so that I can't see the
light coming from the TV.

01:12:11.828 --> 01:12:13.162
Sounds pretty genius, right?

01:12:13.262 --> 01:12:16.466
But, hello, cover the
rest of the stupid door.

01:12:17.600 --> 01:12:19.569
He freaking turns on his big-ass TV,

01:12:19.669 --> 01:12:22.645
and it looks like Immigration's
breaking in to his bedroom.

01:12:24.807 --> 01:12:26.509
And so what happens is he'll stay up

01:12:26.609 --> 01:12:28.511
until 2:00, 3:00,
4:00 in the morning,

01:12:28.611 --> 01:12:31.180
and he, you know,
he's supposed to wake up at 6:00.

01:12:31.280 --> 01:12:34.183
His alarm goes off, and he
sleeps through the alarm,

01:12:34.283 --> 01:12:36.018
and it's a real alarm-alarm.

01:12:36.118 --> 01:12:38.054
It's not a radio. It's freaking...

01:12:38.154 --> 01:12:40.223
(MIMICS ALARM BLARING)

01:12:40.323 --> 01:12:42.161
Whole house awake. Him?

01:12:42.291 --> 01:12:43.834
(SNORING)

01:12:44.293 --> 01:12:45.695
And it's right here.

01:12:45.795 --> 01:12:47.864
So I got to get out of bed,
and I go over to his room,

01:12:47.964 --> 01:12:51.033
and I open the door, and I kick
the stupid towel out of the way,

01:12:51.133 --> 01:12:52.969
and then I walk over, you know.

01:12:53.069 --> 01:12:54.203
(MIMICS ALARM BLARING)

01:12:54.303 --> 01:12:55.371
(MIMICS TURNING OFF ALARM)

01:12:55.471 --> 01:12:57.344
(PANTING)

01:12:58.140 --> 01:13:00.718
And I yell, "Frankie! Frankie!"

01:13:01.143 --> 01:13:02.712
Nothing, so I shake him.

01:13:02.812 --> 01:13:04.380
"Frankie, wake up."

01:13:04.480 --> 01:13:07.116
You know what happens when
I shake my son in the morning?

01:13:07.216 --> 01:13:09.692
It makes him eat in his sleep.

01:13:10.186 --> 01:13:13.196
That's what happens.
I shake him, and he does this.

01:13:23.366 --> 01:13:24.467
So you know what I do?

01:13:24.567 --> 01:13:28.237
I get on top of the bed,
and I slowly lay on top of him,

01:13:28.337 --> 01:13:31.507
and I apply my full weight,
bro, all of it,

01:13:31.607 --> 01:13:33.787
slowly, and you could hear him.

01:13:34.377 --> 01:13:35.920
(GROANING)

01:13:37.380 --> 01:13:42.893
"Oh, God! Oh, God!
You're too big! You're too big!"

01:13:43.252 --> 01:13:44.821
And then I whisper in his ear,

01:13:44.921 --> 01:13:47.226
(WHISPERS)
"That's what your mom said."

01:13:48.357 --> 01:13:50.093
(ALL CHEERING)

01:14:00.937 --> 01:14:04.575
I know one day, my son is going to write
a book called Fluffy's Full of Shit.

01:14:06.375 --> 01:14:08.316
It's kind of crazy.

01:14:09.378 --> 01:14:11.380
I talked to his mom.

01:14:11.480 --> 01:14:14.617
I talked to Frankie's mom,
and she tells me, "Listen."

01:14:14.717 --> 01:14:17.620
She goes, "I'm going to tell
you something. Don't get mad.

01:14:17.720 --> 01:14:21.129
"The reason why you and Frankie
are always butting heads

01:14:22.224 --> 01:14:24.768
"is because you guys are
basically the same person."

01:14:25.394 --> 01:14:26.963
And I go, "We are not
the same person."

01:14:27.063 --> 01:14:28.664
She goes,
"Your mannerisms are the same.

01:14:28.764 --> 01:14:29.966
"The way you guys think is the same.

01:14:30.066 --> 01:14:32.668
"You're exactly...
You're moody in the same way.

01:14:32.768 --> 01:14:33.803
"It's the same."

01:14:33.903 --> 01:14:36.005
And keep in mind,
Frankie's technically my stepson,

01:14:36.105 --> 01:14:37.807
so my girl insisting this,
that we're the same,

01:14:37.907 --> 01:14:40.644
I'm like, "Hello, I wasn't
there at the beginning."

01:14:42.511 --> 01:14:44.981
But, no, she insists.
"You guys are the same."

01:14:45.081 --> 01:14:46.649
And I started analyzing our lives.

01:14:46.749 --> 01:14:48.251
I started analyzing Frankie's life,

01:14:48.351 --> 01:14:49.819
and I started analyzing my life,

01:14:49.919 --> 01:14:51.487
and I started realizing that,
you know what,

01:14:51.587 --> 01:14:54.657
our lives run on these
crazy parallels.

01:14:54.757 --> 01:14:56.425
I'm going to tell you guys something.

01:14:56.525 --> 01:14:59.161
In all my previous specials,
I'd always talk about my mom.

01:14:59.261 --> 01:15:01.230
My mom, my mom, my mom, my mom.

01:15:01.330 --> 01:15:03.666
I never really made
references about my dad,

01:15:03.766 --> 01:15:06.202
because my dad wasn't there
when I was growing up.

01:15:06.302 --> 01:15:07.703
And I made a joke one time

01:15:07.803 --> 01:15:10.039
about how my mom said that
my dad was a mariachi.

01:15:10.139 --> 01:15:11.841
Which is true,
and that he was the guy

01:15:11.941 --> 01:15:13.984
that was on the bottle of hot sauce.

01:15:15.277 --> 01:15:17.548
My dad was the Tapatío guy.

01:15:18.614 --> 01:15:20.850
So after that,

01:15:20.950 --> 01:15:23.753
people started asking
questions about my dad,

01:15:23.853 --> 01:15:25.755
and so they're like, "So what's
the story with your dad?"

01:15:25.855 --> 01:15:27.690
And it felt really awkward
for me to bring up the fact

01:15:27.790 --> 01:15:29.358
that I didn't grow up
with one, you know?

01:15:29.458 --> 01:15:31.527
And nobody wants to tell people,
"I grew up without a parent."

01:15:31.627 --> 01:15:34.297
For me, it was very personal,
and I started building up this wall,

01:15:34.397 --> 01:15:37.733
because people kept asking questions,
especially this one,

01:15:37.833 --> 01:15:41.537
"What would you say if your
dad wanted to see you now?"

01:15:42.338 --> 01:15:44.106
And for me, it's been over 30 years,

01:15:44.206 --> 01:15:45.608
and so I'd always say the same thing.

01:15:45.708 --> 01:15:47.576
I said, "Well, if my
dad wanted to see me,

01:15:47.676 --> 01:15:49.856
"I'd tell him he has
to buy a ticket."

01:15:50.980 --> 01:15:52.214
That was the go-to line.

01:15:52.314 --> 01:15:54.617
"If my dad wants to see me,
I'll tell him to buy a ticket.

01:15:54.717 --> 01:15:56.191
"I'll tell him to buy a ticket.

01:15:56.318 --> 01:15:57.920
"My dad wants to see
me 30 years later,

01:15:58.020 --> 01:16:01.230
"I'm going to have him buy a ticket."
I said this for over seven years.

01:16:01.724 --> 01:16:03.369
And guess who bought a ticket?

01:16:03.592 --> 01:16:04.593
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING)

01:16:04.693 --> 01:16:06.964
Bay Area, it's about to get real.

01:16:08.364 --> 01:16:09.732
Oh, let me tell you this one.

01:16:09.832 --> 01:16:13.169
So I'm doing a show at
a comedy club in LA

01:16:13.269 --> 01:16:14.837
called the Comedy & Magic Club,

01:16:14.937 --> 01:16:17.306
and it's about a 250-seat room,

01:16:17.406 --> 01:16:20.076
and the manager Richard comes
up to me before I go onstage,

01:16:20.176 --> 01:16:21.477
and he goes, "Hey, listen, Gabe.

01:16:21.577 --> 01:16:24.480
"Your dad's in the back of the room.
"Can we pay for his drinks and his food?"

01:16:24.580 --> 01:16:26.615
I go, "What are you talking about?"
He goes, "Yeah, your dad's in the back.

01:16:26.715 --> 01:16:27.917
"Are we paying for
his food and drinks?"

01:16:28.017 --> 01:16:30.186
I go, "Listen, I haven't seen
my dad in over 30 years.

01:16:30.286 --> 01:16:32.088
"That's somebody trying to
get free food and drinks.

01:16:32.188 --> 01:16:33.622
"Cut him off.
Don't pay for anything."

01:16:33.722 --> 01:16:35.591
"Got it, bro." So I go up onstage.

01:16:35.691 --> 01:16:38.963
I start doing my thing.
No problem, show goes over very well.

01:16:39.762 --> 01:16:42.131
I wind up outside after the show,
and I'm doing a meet-and-greet.

01:16:42.231 --> 01:16:44.266
I'm taking pictures,
and I'm signing DVDs.

01:16:44.366 --> 01:16:46.535
My dad goes out and gets in line

01:16:46.635 --> 01:16:49.305
with the rest of the fans
to try to meet me like that.

01:16:49.405 --> 01:16:51.807
And my manager goes
to the back of the line,

01:16:51.907 --> 01:16:53.542
and then she comes up
to me, and she goes,

01:16:53.642 --> 01:16:55.611
"Listen, Gabe. Um...

01:16:55.711 --> 01:16:57.313
"The guy that's at the
back of the line,

01:16:57.413 --> 01:17:01.017
"I have a feeling that
that could be your dad."

01:17:01.117 --> 01:17:03.661
I go, "Really? You, too? Why?"

01:17:03.986 --> 01:17:09.431
"I saw his ID. Gabe,
is his name Jesus?"

01:17:10.126 --> 01:17:14.103
And I was like, "Well, that's a one-in-four
chance right there, you know?"

01:17:15.898 --> 01:17:17.400
I mean, seriously,
you can't throw a rock

01:17:17.500 --> 01:17:20.644
in Los Angeles without hitting
a Jesus. You really can't.

01:17:22.304 --> 01:17:25.408
And so I go, "That's it?"

01:17:25.508 --> 01:17:29.211
She goes, "Gabe, I'm going to be
honest with you. He has your eyes."

01:17:29.311 --> 01:17:32.014
I go, "Really? Out of all of this,

01:17:32.114 --> 01:17:35.317
"you went to the two smallest things
on my body to compare us two?

01:17:35.417 --> 01:17:37.219
"Are you kidding me?"

01:17:37.319 --> 01:17:41.490
And then she said, "Is his
birthday December 25th?"

01:17:41.590 --> 01:17:45.561
And my heart dropped, because my
dad's birthday is actually Christmas.

01:17:45.661 --> 01:17:46.929
Every year, my mom would remind me,

01:17:47.029 --> 01:17:50.366
"Merry Christmas. He's not
here again. Open your gift."

01:17:50.466 --> 01:17:52.034
And so it always stuck right here,

01:17:52.134 --> 01:17:54.537
"December 25th, December 25th,
December 25th."

01:17:54.637 --> 01:17:58.841
So it freaked me out so bad that I
started shaking. I started shaking.

01:17:58.941 --> 01:18:01.143
I was freaking out, because it was
a bunch of emotions. I was angry.

01:18:01.244 --> 01:18:04.113
I was sad. I was happy. It was just
everything all at the same time.

01:18:04.213 --> 01:18:06.415
And so people are coming up to me.
They're like, "Are you okay?"

01:18:06.515 --> 01:18:08.017
And I kept saying this over and over.

01:18:08.117 --> 01:18:10.920
I said, "My dad's here. My dad's here.
My dad's here. My dad's here."

01:18:11.020 --> 01:18:13.055
And they're like, "That's good.
Your dad's here to support you."

01:18:13.155 --> 01:18:14.690
I'm like, "I haven't seen
him in over 30 years."

01:18:14.790 --> 01:18:17.436
And they're like, "Awkward.
Yeah. Awkward."

01:18:18.661 --> 01:18:21.030
So I told my manager, "Go to the
back of the line and get him out.

01:18:21.130 --> 01:18:23.199
"This is not the time or the
place to do this, right?"

01:18:23.299 --> 01:18:25.301
So she goes back there,
and I see them talking.

01:18:25.401 --> 01:18:27.703
Then I see him walking away,
and then he stops,

01:18:27.803 --> 01:18:31.040
and he turns around, and he
looks at me, and he waves.

01:18:31.140 --> 01:18:32.944
And it freaked me out, you guys.

01:18:33.409 --> 01:18:36.879
In addition to freaking me out,
he's holding one of my DVDs,

01:18:36.979 --> 01:18:40.716
which really messed me up,
because I've been signing DVDs all night.

01:18:40.816 --> 01:18:42.393
What was I going to put on his?

01:18:43.485 --> 01:18:46.029
You know? "Hey, where you been?"

01:18:51.060 --> 01:18:53.395
So she gets his info, gives it to me.

01:18:53.495 --> 01:18:56.332
I give the info to my girlfriend,
right, and I finish the meet-and-greet.

01:18:56.432 --> 01:18:58.000
We get in the car. We go back home.

01:18:58.100 --> 01:18:59.902
I'm not saying anything.
I'm just shaking.

01:19:00.002 --> 01:19:01.837
I'm sweating, and my
girl goes, "You okay?"

01:19:01.937 --> 01:19:02.938
I said, "Listen, you know what?

01:19:03.038 --> 01:19:05.908
"I been playing this scenario
in my head for over 30 years,

01:19:06.008 --> 01:19:07.409
"what would I do if
he ever showed up.

01:19:07.509 --> 01:19:09.078
"I thought I was
prepared to handle this,

01:19:09.178 --> 01:19:10.913
"and I'm not. I'm freaking out."

01:19:11.013 --> 01:19:13.249
And she goes, "Baby, listen,
how 'bout we sleep on it,

01:19:13.349 --> 01:19:14.950
"and we'll figure this
out together tomorrow?

01:19:15.050 --> 01:19:17.820
"Just sleep on it. Try to relax."
And I'm like, "That's a good idea."

01:19:17.920 --> 01:19:19.321
So we get in bed.

01:19:19.421 --> 01:19:21.857
She knocks out, and I'm just...
I can't. I can't sleep.

01:19:21.957 --> 01:19:25.361
And 3:00 in the morning rolls around,
and I say, "I can't take it anymore."

01:19:25.461 --> 01:19:27.129
So I wake up my girl.
I said, "Baby, get up."

01:19:27.229 --> 01:19:30.103
"What is it? What?"
I go, "Listen, call him."

01:19:30.366 --> 01:19:32.601
"Right now?" I go, "Yes."

01:19:32.701 --> 01:19:36.610
"It's 3:00 in the morning.
That's disrespectful."

01:19:37.406 --> 01:19:40.348
I'm like, "Hello.
Who waited 30 years?"

01:19:41.243 --> 01:19:44.980
"Fine." So she gets on the
phone, and she calls my dad,

01:19:45.080 --> 01:19:46.849
and he answered on the first ring,

01:19:46.949 --> 01:19:49.518
and I could hear 'em talking,
going back and forth.

01:19:49.618 --> 01:19:51.053
And then she hangs up
the phone, and she says,

01:19:51.153 --> 01:19:54.023
"Listen, baby, your dad
wants me to let you know

01:19:54.123 --> 01:19:56.859
"that he doesn't want any money.
He doesn't want any money.

01:19:56.959 --> 01:20:00.296
"He doesn't want anything from you,
but 10 minutes of your time,

01:20:00.396 --> 01:20:02.231
"so he can ask you a
couple of questions

01:20:02.331 --> 01:20:04.466
"and hopefully answer some questions.

01:20:04.566 --> 01:20:08.976
"Me, personally, I think you need closure,
because you're messed up."

01:20:11.907 --> 01:20:14.018
My girl keeps it real.

01:20:14.610 --> 01:20:17.290
So I said, "Listen, call him back.

01:20:17.579 --> 01:20:18.881
"Let him know that I
want to see him today

01:20:18.981 --> 01:20:20.182
"at the comedy club where we met."

01:20:20.282 --> 01:20:22.184
She goes, "Fine."
So she calls him back.

01:20:22.284 --> 01:20:25.487
She hangs up the phone. And she goes,
"Okay, baby, I confirmed it.

01:20:25.587 --> 01:20:28.691
"7:00 at the comedy club.
Can we get some sleep now?"

01:20:28.791 --> 01:20:30.659
And I go, "Listen,
I got to do something."

01:20:30.759 --> 01:20:34.863
She goes, "What?" And I get out of bed,
and I walk over to the living room.

01:20:34.963 --> 01:20:37.666
And in the living room,
I have a giant mirror, okay?

01:20:37.766 --> 01:20:39.835
And this giant mirror,
I get in front of it,

01:20:39.935 --> 01:20:43.105
and I start rehearsing the speech
I'm about to have with my dad

01:20:43.205 --> 01:20:46.508
that I haven't seen in over 30 years.
Now keep in mind, you guys.

01:20:46.608 --> 01:20:51.347
This is the only thing I've ever really
rehearsed. I can't rehearse this,

01:20:51.447 --> 01:20:55.017
